# Information Security Overview

## What is Information Security?

Information Security (InfoSec) is the practice of protecting information from unauthorized access, modification, disclosure, or destruction.

The main objectives of information security are commonly known as the CIA Triad:

### Confidentiality
Ensuring that information is accessible only to authorized individuals.

### Integrity
Ensuring that information remains accurate and unaltered.

### Availability
Ensuring that information is available when needed by authorized users.

## Importance of Information Security

As digital systems become increasingly integrated into everyday life, protecting sensitive information has become essential. Information security helps prevent data breaches, cyberattacks, identity theft, and unauthorized access to confidential information.

## Security Techniques

Several techniques are used to protect information and systems:

### Encryption

Encryption converts readable information into an unreadable format. Only authorized users with the correct key can access the original data.


## Relation to Steganography

Steganography is one of the techniques used in information security. While encryption protects the content of a message, steganography hides the existence of the message itself. Together, these techniques can provide stronger protection for sensitive information.
